column2: GoBiFO/ Capacity Building for Strengthening Social Capital in SL Special JSDF Facility for Facilitating Future Sustainability
column19:
This document includes mention of GoBiFO, World Bank, and Japan Social Development Fund; it seems to be the correct project.
"In 2005, the GoSL secured a grant from the Japan Social Development Fund (administered by the World Bank) to undertake a pilot project focusing on ‘capacity development to strengthen social capital’. The funds have been used to implement community-driven development (CDD) projects in the Bombali and Bonthe Districts." (pdf p 12)

column2: GoBiFO/ Capacity Building for Strengthening Social Capital in SL Special JSDF Facility for Facilitating Future Sustainability
column19:
This document includes mention of GoBiFO, World Bank, and Japan Social Development Fund; it seems to be the correct project.
"In 2005, the GoSL secured a grant from the Japan Social Development Fund (administered by the World Bank) to undertake a pilot project focusing on ‘capacity development to strengthen social capital’. The funds have been used to implement community-driven development (CDD) projects in the Bombali and Bonthe Districts." (pdf p 12)

No specific locations provided, this project appears to affect the public and private sectors, farmers, and "rural communities and local governments", coding this as a nationwide locally-dispersed project
No specific location information provided, this is a countrywide project taking place at the local level
